ping each other out.  At 33 you would certainly need a group.  I got in a group that was camping Gabbie Mardoodle.  Screwed my faction with them but I'm rebuilding it in SolB. <p>Lourre Nytblytr<BR>41st <a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/pon/>Paladin</a> of Tunare<BR>Lord of Swords<BR><a href=http://www.eqcrosswinds.com>Court of the Crosswinds</a><BR><a href=http://www.ralloszek.net>Rallos Zek</a><BR><BR>"Far better it is to dare mighty things, to win glorious triumphs, even though checkered by failure...than to rank with those poor spirits who neither enjoy much nor suffer much, because they live in a gray twilight that knows not victory nor defeat." - Theodore Roosevelt</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucarmaris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carmaris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/8/01 7:38:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2974.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting Melatite in Sol A</span><hr size=1> Only CB's and CC's drop Melatite.  Deep in gnome fortress is best spot, sometimes get lucky near entrances/exits to gnome area, but that's rare.  If you can't get groups willing to go in, just zone in occassionally and /auction WTB melatite.  If I'm in sola jacking around and someone does that, I normally just give it to them....<br><br>Carmaris Stoneheart<br>52 Dorf Cavalier of Avvisione<br>Bertoxxulous<br><br>Oh, btw, I got several levels in solb before I killed my first clockwork.  Now, after numerous boredom camps fire elemental/gabbie/exg, I'm still warmly to the little folk in sola (though I'm sure I'm dorf kebabs if I ever set foot in Ak'anon).  I need to jog over there tonight and see if maybe they consider me an ally....hehe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulourrenytblytr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lourre Nytblytr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/8/01 8:43:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2974.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting Melatite in Sol A</span><hr size=1> The MB, MC, XB, and XC also drop melatite.  I have seen all of them drop it, some more rare, though. <p>Lourre Nytblytr<BR>41st <a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/pon/>Paladin</a> of Tunare<BR>Lord of Swords<BR><a href=http://www.eqcrosswinds.com>Court of the Crosswinds</a><BR><a href=http://www.ralloszek.net>Rallos Zek</a><BR><BR>"Far better it is to dare mighty things, to win glorious triumphs, even though checkered by failure...than to rank with those poor spirits who neither enjoy much nor suffer much, because they live in a gray twilight that knows not victory nor defeat." - Theodore Roosevelt</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwyrmbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>wyrmbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/8/01 9:03:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2974.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/oddnfun/wyrmbane_sml.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting Melatite in Sol A</span><hr size=1> <br>The last time I went hunting for Maletite, i decided I didn't want much of a faction hit.  To mitigate the faction loses, and keep the kills to a minimum I killed ONLY Clockwork MB's and MC's.  My preference is to kill only MC's, and only MB's if there are no MC's around.   I have had a Maletite drop on every kill of an MC, but I may have been lucky.<br><br>Another tip.   Head into Sol B and kill a bunch of Kobolds first.  It will bring up your faction before you start clockwork killing.  If there are no MC's or MB's up when I go through the entire Gnome Castle, i just leave and come back later.<br><br>wyrmbane<br>Paladin of the 49th Crusade<br>Hand of Mana<br>The Nameless<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uabazagaroth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Abazagaroth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/9/01 9:31:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2974.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting Melatite in Sol A</span><hr size=1> Bottom line, at 33, bring some friends. You MIGHT be able to solo a bit at 35 to 37 or so, but will be tough. Also, melatite drops off of ANY clockwork whose code ends in B or C. I have &lt;b&gt;personally&lt;/b&gt; gotten it off of CB, CC, MB, MC, XB, and XC. The best way to solo for it when they are still blue is zone into SolA, head down the path, past the swinging axe thing, up to the area that opens up into the pit. On this ledge you can go left or right, on your left (unless someone is killing them) will be two gobs, head that way. Hug the right wall in the tunnel and you shouldn't aggro the other gobs, and then you'll see a single clockwork.<br><br>That one is a safe kill, but make sure to *root*. Also, if it breaks root and runs, cast stun first then root, stun has a shorter casting time and you'll get it off before the thing gets out of range, and the stun lasts long enough to recast root. If it gets away, just &lt;b&gt;stay&lt;/b&gt; 9 times out of 10 it won't bring anything back with it. Just heal yourself in that respite and get ready to root when it comes back.<br><br>Then, go out onto the bridge thing over the lava, that clockwork isn't safe to kill until you get to 40 or so, so leave it. Once off the bridge you have two options, go straight where there is a live gnome and a single clockwork, or take a left dow by the lava and another single clockwork. Go left. Now you are by a door, and inside you have another clockwork, then a door, and a room with two clockworks. A wanderer walks through here. now here is the strategy. Go back out the door, and head up the stairs towards the goblins (they won't aggro until you get right on top of them). Sit there and watch the hallway for the wanderer. When it comes by, target it, and let it go. Stay there for maybe two minutes and start hitting stun. If the target is out of range you don't eat up your mana, and when it gets in range the first few casts won't hit (waste a tiny bit of mana), but you will get a cast off &lt;b&gt;before&lt;/b&gt; it comes into site and the cast will go off before it goes through the door. The single clockwork will then run up to you, and you can keep up there away from anything else.<br><br>Now you can safely go and pull the single clockwork through the door, and pull up to where you just killed the wanderer. If you are careful, you can even single pull the one clockwork near the lava that you passed to get to that hallway. Sometimes that will pull others though.<br><br>Rinse and repeat, and you have 3 or 4 spawns you can kill over and over to get the ones that drop the melatite to spawn. Melatite does &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; always drop either. Seems like one in 3 or one in 4 from personal experience. I have killed these things for hours upon hours starting from apprehensive faction, and they are still dubious. So don't waste time worrying about the faction loss. This is also good solo exp once you hit 39 or so until you hit 42, when you can more easily kill them at a rate to make it worthwhile.<br><br>Also, the &quot;B&quot; types cast force shock so back up against a corner when fighting them, and the &quot;C&quot; ones cast a wimpy cold spell, which doesn't matter because it only hits for less than 20 anyway, while the clockworks will hit you for far more in normal melee.<br><br>So that's how to solo melatite but I suggest you just get a group to go with you, is much easier.<br><br>Abazagaroth<br><br> <p>C. David Kreger, Pennsylvania State University<br>Webmaster:<br><a href="http://www.humanevolution.f2s.com" target="_top">A Look at Modern Human Origins</a><br>Moderator:<br><a href="http://www3.cybercities.com/h/humanorigins/webring.html" target="_top">Paleoanthropology Web Resources Webring</a><br>Moderator:<br><a href="http://pub19.ezboard.com/balookatmodernhumanorigins" target="_top">Human Evolution Message Board</a></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showPrevMessage?topicID=2974.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showNextMessage?topicID=2974.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2974.topic&index=5><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.emailToFriend?topicID=2974.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><b